+{"parentUuid":"83672c96-8a75-4e54-810f-021db07552a8","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"329d4287-5a4c-4ce5-b23b-fa1ffcd1f813","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cozy-spinning-otter","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SpzkJzjjoEJEyeNQnxtZ2L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n     2→\n     3→Add the ability to shut down the task queue system in an orderly fashion.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- A shutdown operation should signal the system to stop accepting new tasks.\n     8→- After shutdown is initiated, attempting to add new tasks should produce an error.\n     9→- The shutdown should wait for all currently-processing tasks to finish, up to a configurable timeout.\n    10→- If processing tasks do not complete within the timeout, they should be force-cancelled.\n    11→- Callbacks can be registered to run during the shutdown process.\n    12→- The shutdown should produce a summary indicating how many tasks completed, how many were force-cancelled, and how long the shutdown took.\n    13→- Calling shutdown multiple times should be safe and return the same result.\n    14→- If no tasks are processing, shutdown should complete immediately.\n    15→"}]},"uuid":"b1d463c0-2d1d-460b-8a7a-38df3af49448","timestamp":"2026-03-10T15:57:40.738Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"","agentId":"acc2a241e95b0ec32"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01SuLGbngZdLxvFVvfYrcejG","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01CGeYXZtEUCtxapBm3Updxn","uuid":"ee5d9077-9360-4cf5-9168-4a9229cbf8d7","timestamp":"2026-03-10T15:57:40.746Z"}
+{"parentUuid":"30d048c4-54ab-4293-a8f6-872a62506f31","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/workspace","sessionId":"329d4287-5a4c-4ce5-b23b-fa1ffcd1f813","version":"2.1.63","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cozy-spinning-otter","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CGeYXZtEUCtxapBm3Updxn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have thoroughly explored the entire project. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Structure Overview\n\n### Workspace Root Files\n\n1. **TASK.md** - Main project description:\n   - Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch\n   - 12 phases of increasing sophistication\n   - API exported from `src/index.ts`\n   - No external runtime dependencies allowed\n   - Must pass build and lint checks\n\n2. **package.json** - Project configuration:\n   - Name: \"bench-task-queue\"\n   - Type: \"module\" (ES modules)\n   - Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n   - Dev dependencies: TypeScript 5.4, ESLint, Vitest, TypeScript ESLint\n\n3. **tsconfig.json** - TypeScript configuration:\n   - Target: ES2022\n   - Module: Node16\n   - Output: ./dist\n   - Root: ./src\n   - Strict mode enabled\n   - Declaration maps and source maps enabled\n\n4. **.eslintrc.cjs** - ESLint configuration:\n   - Parser: @typescript-eslint/parser\n   - Extends: eslint:recommended + TypeScript rules\n   - Unused vars ignored if prefixed with underscore\n\n5. **vitest.config.ts** - Test configuration:\n   - Global test utilities enabled\n   - Test timeout: 10000ms\n\n6. **.gitignore** - Ignores: node_modules/, dist/, *.tsbuildinfo\n\n### Source Structure\n\n**src/** - Currently empty except for .gitkeep (ready for implementation)\n\n### Phase Requirements (12 Phases)\n\n**Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue**\n- Add tasks with payload, receive task objects with UUID, status, and timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state, transition to \"processing\" when retrieved\n- FIFO retrieval, returns null if empty\n- Check queue size\n\n**Phase 2: Named Queues**\n- Multiple independent queues identified by name\n- Default queue if no name specified\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n**Phase 3: Priority**\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1 = highest, 5 = default)\n- Higher priority tasks returned first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Invalid priorities cause errors\n\n**Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks**\n- Specify delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed preferred over unavailable delayed\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered by availability time, then priority, then FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n\n**Phase 5: Retry with Backoff**\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (default 1s, 2s, 4s...)\n- Default max 3 retries (configurable)\n- Default baseDelay 1000ms (configurable)\n- Track attempt count\n- Keep queue and priority on retry\n- Failed state after exhausted retries\n\n**Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue**\n- Tasks with exhausted retries move to DLQ\n- View dead-lettered tasks for a queue\n- Retain error info and failure count\n- Ability to move DLQ tasks back to original queue\n- Clear DLQ for a queue\n- Each named queue has own DLQ\n\n**Phase 7: Task Dependencies**\n- Specify task IDs that must complete before task becomes available\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- Check unblocked status when dependency completes\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't auto-fail dependents\n- Query dependency status\n\n**Phase 8: Concurrency Control**\n- Per-queue maximum concurrency limit\n- If limit reached, retrieving returns null even if pending tasks exist\n- Default: no limit (unlimited)\n- Complete/fail task frees a slot\n- Query limit and current active count\n- Interacts correctly with priority\n\n**Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation**\n- Processing task reports progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with notifications\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending/processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Phase 10: Recurring Tasks**\n- Schedule cron expressions with queue and task template\n- Simple cron subset:\n  - `*/N * * * *` (every N minutes)\n  - `0 * * * *` (every hour on the hour)\n  - `0 0 * * *` (every day at midnight)\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism for testing\n- Once enqueued, subject to all queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future creation\n\n**Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline**\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Task passes through all middleware in order\n- Each middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Can modify task (metadata, payload transformation)\n- If no \"next\", skip processing\n- Throw error marks task as failed\n- Register processing handler per queue\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n**Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown**\n- Signal system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Error when adding tasks after shutdown\n- Wait for processing tasks (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel if timeout exceeded\n- Register callbacks during shutdown\n- Return summary: completed count, force-cancelled count, duration\n- Safe to call shutdown multiple times\n- Immediate if no processing tasks\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Considerations from Requirements\n\n1. **Extensibility**: Later phases require rethinking early decisions; design with extensibility in mind\n2. **Task Identity**: Each task needs unique identifier and lifecycle status tracking\n3. **Feature Interactions**: Priorities, delays, dependencies, concurrency all interact\n4. **Per-Queue Independence**: Each queue operates independently with own rules\n5. **Backward Compatibility**: Phase 2+ must remain compatible with earlier phases\n6. **Error Handling**: Invalid inputs (priority, circular dependencies) must cause errors\n7. **Testing**: No external dependencies; write tests as you go\n\nAll files are available and ready for implementation in `/workspace/src/`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acc2a241e95b0ec32 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 23257\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 27013</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"b024e25b-d76e-414d-814d-56a84dbc0932","timestamp":"2026-03-10T15:57:56.609Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire project structure. I need to understand:\n1. All files in the workspace root (package.json, tsconfig.json, etc.)\n2. All phase requirement files in phases/*.md\n3. Any existing source files in src/\n4. The full content of TASK.md\n\nRead ALL phase files (phases/01.md through phases/12.md) and ALL config files. Be very thorough - read every single file.","agentId":"acc2a241e95b0ec32","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have thoroughly explored the entire project. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Structure Overview\n\n### Workspace Root Files\n\n1. **TASK.md** - Main project description:\n   - Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch\n   - 12 phases of increasing sophistication\n   - API exported from `src/index.ts`\n   - No external runtime dependencies allowed\n   - Must pass build and lint checks\n\n2. **package.json** - Project configuration:\n   - Name: \"bench-task-queue\"\n   - Type: \"module\" (ES modules)\n   - Scripts: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint), `test` (vitest run)\n   - Dev dependencies: TypeScript 5.4, ESLint, Vitest, TypeScript ESLint\n\n3. **tsconfig.json** - TypeScript configuration:\n   - Target: ES2022\n   - Module: Node16\n   - Output: ./dist\n   - Root: ./src\n   - Strict mode enabled\n   - Declaration maps and source maps enabled\n\n4. **.eslintrc.