w I'm thinking through what happens when middleware doesn't call next—the task gets stuck in 'processing' state since it was already dequeued. The requirement says to skip processing if next isn't called, so maybe the task should just complete without running the handler, or stay in processing and let the user handle it manually.\n\nActually, looking at how Express middleware works, if middleware doesn't call next, it's essentially filtering or handling the task itself. In that case, completing the task makes sense since it's been handled, even if the main handler never ran.\n\nLet me think through the logic: processNext should auto-complete the task unless it was explicitly failed or cancelled. That way, whether middleware skips the handler or the handler runs, the task gets marked complete. I'm trying to figure out what the test would look like to validate this behavior.\n\nWriting test code... I need to stop overthinking this and just implement it. For the shutdown callbacks in Phase 12, I'm thinking `onShutdown(callback)` is the right approach—register callbacks that execute during the shutdown process. Let me finalize the API surface across all the phases...\n\nDefining the method signatures... I've mapped out the complete API across twelve phases, and now I'm ready to implement it. I'm going to write the code myself rather than splitting it across a team since the components are tightly interconnected and need to work together seamlessly. I'll start with the type definitions, then the cron utilities, the main task queue implementation, and finally the public API exports, followed by a build and lint pass to catch any issues.\n\nWriting the implementation files...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1771,"cache_read_input_tokens":22127,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1771,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_avai